sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant C as Client (Auditor)
    participant AC as AlertsController
    participant AS as AlertsService
    participant AR as AlertsRepository
    participant DB as Database

    Note over C,DB: 1 · Consulta de alertas ativos — RF028 · RF029 · RF039 · RN11 · RN12

    loop Polling periódico (auditor em turno)
        C->>+AC: GET /audit/alerts?event_id={id}
        Note over AC: requireAuth — JWT obrigatório
        AC->>+AS: getAlerts(event_id)
        AS->>+AR: findAlerts(event_id)
        AR->>+DB: SELECT shifts + checkpoints p/ detectar inconsistências
        Note over DB: Verifica: turno sem checkpoint há >5min (RN11),<br/>corredor sem rotação (RN12), km negativo (RN25)
        DB-->>-AR: rows de turnos + checkpoints
        AR-->>-AS: alertsData[]
        AS->>AS: classify(alertsData) → { type, severity, shift_id, athlete_name }
        AS-->>-AC: alerts[]
        AC-->>-C: 200 { alerts: [ { type, message, shift_id, athlete_name, since } ] }
    end

    Note over C,DB: 2 · Nenhum alerta ativo

    C->>+AC: GET /audit/alerts?event_id={id}
    AC->>+AS: getAlerts(event_id)
    AS->>+AR: findAlerts(event_id)
    AR->>+DB: SELECT ...
    DB-->>-AR: [] (vazio)
    AR-->>-AS: []
    AS-->>-AC: []
    AC-->>-C: 200 { alerts: [] }

    Note over C,DB: 3 · event_id ausente ou inválido

    C->>+AC: GET /audit/alerts (sem event_id)
    AC-->>-C: 400 { error: "event_id obrigatório" }
